---
# NashR Shared Agent Rules
alwaysApply: true
---

## 1. Branching & Sync
- Always sync before starting:
  - `git checkout production`
  - `git pull origin production`
- Create feature branch:
  - `git checkout -b cursor/<short-description>`

## 2. Safety Constraints (CRITICAL)
- NEVER deploy to:
  - `LIVE`
  - `DEMO`
- Only operate in:
  - local
  - backtesting
  - CI

## 3. Change Classification
### Small Changes
- Logging
- Refactor (no logic change)
- Config/UI
- Action: run `make test-fast`

### Non-Trivial Changes (MANDATORY)
Includes:
- Entry / Exit
- Risk / Position sizing
- Execution
- Reconciliation
- Strategy logic
- Required:
  - `python3 app/backtesting/backtest.py --days 7 --all`

## 4. Validation Pipeline
Before PR:
1. `make test-fast`
2. `make test-integration` (if needed)
3. Backtest (if non-trivial)

## 5. Pull Request Rules
- Must include:
  - Summary
  - Risk level: Low / Medium / High
  - Backtest result (if applicable)
- Target:
  - `production`

## 6. Slack Notification
After PR send:
- PR link
- Summary
- Risk level
- Backtest result

## 7. Failure Handling
If:
- Tests fail
- Backtest worse than before
- Errors occur

Then:
- STOP
- DO NOT create PR
- Report logs + reason
